{"title_page": "DanTDM", "text_new": "{{short description|British professional gamer and YouTuber}}\n{{Use British English|date=November 2016}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{Infobox YouTube personality\n| name            = DanTDM\n[[File:Hello sisters|thumb|what is up my dudes]]\n| image           = DanTDM2019.jpg\n| caption         = Middleton in 2019\n| birth_name      = Daniel Robert Middleton\n| birth_date      = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1991|11|8}}\n| birth_place     = [[Aldershot]], England\n| nationality     = British\n| residence       = [[Wellingborough]], England\n| occupation      = {{flatlist|\n* [[YouTuber]]\n* [[Let's Play|video game commentator]]\n}}\n| spouse          = {{marriage|Jemma Middleton|17 March 2013}}\n<!-- please do not add 'children' here, it is not a parameter in this template (see [[Template:Infobox YouTube personality]]) -->\n| pseudonym       = TheDiamondMinecart\n\n| channels        = {{flatlist|\n* [https://www.youtube.com/user/TheDiamondMinecart DanTDM]\n* [https://www.youtube.com/user/MoreTDM  MoreTDM]\n* [https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCa94pyq0HNK8qAFUBJiVAeA DanTDM Live]\n}}\n| years_active    = 2012\u2013present<!-- year of primary channel's creation until its discontinuation or present day -->\n| genre           = [[Video game culture|Gaming]] (focus on [[Minecraft]] and [[Fortnite]])\n| subscribers     = 22.6 million\n| views           = 16.5 billion <!-- round down to nearest .1 billion -->\n| stats_update    = 4 April 2020\n| silver_button   = yes\n| silver_year     = 2013<ref name=\"100k subscribers\">{{Cite AV media |url=//www.youtube.com/watch?v=bWOdn2C1PDc |title=TDM Vlogs \u2013 100,000 Subscribers, IRL & Events! |date=25 June 2013 |access-date=21 August 2016}}</ref>\n| gold_button     = yes\n| gold_year       = 2013<ref>{{Cite AV media |url=//www.youtube.com/watch?v=zk2_xuP4TNE |title=YouTube's Golden Award! \u2013 TheDiamondMinecart |date=17 September 2014 |last=The Diamond Minecart // DanTDM |access-date=11 February 2016 |via=YouTube}}</ref>\n| diamond_button  = yes\n| diamond_year    = 2016<ref>{{Cite web |url=//www.youtube.com/watch?v=IyJQInF9TiE |title=10 Million Subscribers!!!! |last=TheDiamondMinecart: DanTDM |date=28 March 2016 |via=YouTube |access-date=8 June 2016}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=//www.youtube.com/watch?v=30VbbiWSmHA |title=Our Diamond Play Button!!!! |last=TheDiamondMinecart: DanTDM |date=30 July 2016 |via=YouTube |access-date=30 July 2016}}</ref>\n}}\n'''Daniel Robert Middleton'''<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://beta.companieshouse.gov.uk/officers/7QepmF7pYH55RvCFGf2Utfw36GU/appointments |title=Daniel Robert MIDDLETON - Personal Appointments (free information from Companies House) |website=beta.companieshouse.gov.uk |access-date=10 January 2018}}</ref> (born 8 November 1991), known online as '''DanTDM''' (formerly '''The Diamond Minecart'''), is a British [[YouTuber|YouTube personality]] and professional gamer. His online video channels have covered many video games, mainly the popular games ''[[Minecraft]]'', ''[[Roblox]]'', and ''[[Pok\u00e9mon]]''.\n\nHis channel has been listed among the top YouTube channels in the [[United Kingdom]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://socialblade.com/youtube/top/country/gb/mostsubscribed |title=Top 100 YouTubers in United Kingdom Filtered by Subscribers |website=socialblade.com |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160330110614/http://socialblade.com/youtube/top/country/gb/mostsubscribed |archive-date=30 March 2016 |access-date=28 March 2016 }}</ref> In July 2015, he was listed as one of the most popular YouTubers in the world by viewership.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Dredge |first=Stuart |url=https://www.theguardian.com/technology/2015/aug/31/the-diamond-minecart-pewdiepie-youtube-minecraft |title=The Diamond Minecart becomes most popular YouTube channel |date=1 September 2015 |work=The Guardian |access-date=11 February 2016}}</ref> He has won several [[Kids' Choice Awards]] and set [[Guinness World Records]] for his gaming and presenting. In 2017, Middleton topped the [[Forbes]] list of Highest-Paid YouTube Stars, earning $16.5 million (about {{GBP|12.2 million}}) in one year.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.forbes.com/pictures/5a275d6931358e286471a7e8/1-daniel-middleton-dantdm/#28a09833343e |title=The World's Highest-Paid YouTube Stars 2017 |website=Forbes |publisher=Forbes |access-date=7 December 2017}}</ref> {{As of|2020|2|df=}}, Middleton has over 16 billion views, around 22.5 million subscribers and has posted more than 3,400 videos.\n\n==Early life==\nDaniel Middleton was born on 8 November 1991 in [[Aldershot]], England as the elder son of two siblings.<ref name=\"DrawMyLife\">{{Cite web |url=//www.youtube.com/watch?v=N2D9Y6lSFkw |title=Draw My Life - TheDiamondMinecart &#124; 1,000,000 Subscriber Special |last=DanTDM |date=10 December 2013 |publisher=YouTube |access-date=7 February 2015}}</ref> His parents divorced when he was little.<ref name=\"DrawMyLife\" /> He attended the [[University of Nottingham]], and started a YouTube channel in 2009 dedicated to [[Counter-Strike Global Offensive]] while at university, in which he called himself \"PokemanDanlvl45\".<ref>{{Cite web |url=//www.youtube.com/user/PokemanDanLv45 |title=PokemanDanLv45 |website=YouTube |access-date=20 March 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\nIn 2012, Middleton created ''The Diamond Minecart'', a gaming channel.<ref name=\"bbc 20140411\">{{Cite news |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-england-northamptonshire-26990297 |title=Dan Middleton's Minecraft videos a global hit |date=11 April 2014 |access-date=3 March 2016 |publisher=BBC News}}</ref> He changed his channel's name into ''TheDiamondMinecart // DanTDM'', and then, in 12 December 2016, to ''DanTDM''.<ref>{{Cite web |url=//www.youtube.com/watch?v=_mCiZxmZ7dQ |title=I'M CHANGING MY NAME... |last=DanTDM |date=12 December 2016 |via=YouTube |access-date=1 April 2017}}</ref>{{efn|Although DanTDM's channel name has changed, the channel still lists itself as TheDiamondMinecart within its URL.}} He currently produces videos out of his home studio in [[Wellingborough]].<ref name=\"bbc 20140411\" />\n\nHe released a graphic novel called ''[[Trayaurus and the Enchanted Crystal]]'' on 6 October 2016.<ref name=\"glou 20161012\" /><ref>{{Cite news |last=Cowdrey |first=Katherine |url=http://www.thebookseller.com/news/trapeze-publish-graphic-novel-youtubes-dan-diamond-minecart-330271 |title=YouTube's Dan the Diamond Minecart inks book deal - The Bookseller |work=The Bookseller |access-date=13 August 2016 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160826212251/http://www.thebookseller.com/news/trapeze-publish-graphic-novel-youtubes-dan-diamond-minecart-330271 |archive-date=26 August 2016 }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.publishersweekly.com/pw/by-topic/new-titles/on-sale-calendar/article/71090-the-on-sale-calendar-october-2016-children-s-books.html |title=The On-Sale Calendar October 2016 Children's Books |last=Staff |date=3 August 2016 |website=[[Publishers Weekly]] |access-date=13 August 2016}}</ref> The novel remained at the number one spot on [[The New York Times Best Seller list|''The New York Times'' Best Seller list]] for hardcover graphic books for eleven weeks.<ref>Listings on ''The New York Times'' Best Seller list per week: [https://www.nytimes.com/books/best-sellers/2016/11/13/hardcover-graphic-books/ Week 1], [https://www.nytimes.com/books/best-sellers/2016/11/20/hardcover-graphic-books/ Week 2], [https://www.nytimes.com/books/best-sellers/2016/11/27/hardcover-graphic-books/ Week 3], [https://www.nytimes.com/books/best-sellers/2016/12/04/hardcover-graphic-books/ Week 4], [https://www.nytimes.com/books/best-sellers/2016/12/11/hardcover-graphic-books/ Week 5], [https://www.nytimes.com/books/best-sellers/2016/12/18/hardcover-graphic-books/ Week 6], [https://www.nytimes.com/books/best-sellers/2016/12/25/hardcover-graphic-books/ Week 7], [https://www.nytimes.com/books/best-sellers/2017/01/01/hardcover-graphic-books/ Week 8], [https://www.nytimes.com/books/best-sellers/2017/01/08/hardcover-graphic-books/ Week 9], [https://www.nytimes.com/books/best-sellers/2017/01/15/hardcover-graphic-books/ Week 10], [https://www.nytimes.com/books/best-sellers/2017/01/22/hardcover-graphic-books/ Week 11], [https://www.nytimes.com/books/best-sellers/2017/01/29/hardcover-graphic-books/ Week 12, when it fell to the second spot].</ref> He was a featured guest at the [[Cheltenham Literature Festival]] and went on a book tour that included parts of the UK and a visit to [[New York City]].<ref name=\"glou 20161012\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.gloucestershirelive.co.uk/bet-you-haven-8217-t-heard-of-the-biggest-star-at-the-cheltenham-literature-festival-2016/story-29780498-detail/story.html |title=Bet you've not heard of the biggest star at literature festival? |last=Merrell |first=Andrew |date=5 October 2016 |website=Gloucestershire Live |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161012152035/http://www.gloucestershirelive.co.uk/bet-you-haven-8217-t-heard-of-the-biggest-star-at-the-cheltenham-literature-festival-2016/story-29780498-detail/story.html |archive-date=12 October 2016 |access-date=12 October 2016 }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.gloucestershirelive.co.uk/hundreds-rush-waterstones-tent-at-cheltenham-literature-festival-to-get-a-glimpse-of-dantdm/story-29799439-detail/story.html |title=Hundreds rush Cheltenham Literature Festival tent to reach DanTDM |last=Merrell |first=Andrew |date=11 October 2016 |website=Gloucestershire Live |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161012235110/http://www.gloucestershirelive.co.uk/hundreds-rush-waterstones-tent-at-cheltenham-literature-festival-to-get-a-glimpse-of-dantdm/story-29799439-detail/story.html |archive-date=12 October 2016 |access-date=12 October 2016 }}</ref><ref name=\"geek dad\">{{Cite web |url=https://geekdad.com/2016/11/dantdms-new-graphic-novel/ |title=Take 'Minecraft' to the Next (Reading) Level With DanTDM's New Graphic Novel - GeekDad |last=Knox |first=Kelly |date=25 November 2016 |website=geekdad.com |access-date=21 September 2017}}</ref><ref>{{Cite tweet |number=790996720717008896 |user=dantdm |title=MY BOOK IN THE U.S. & MINI U.S. BOOK TOUR!!!: http://youtu.be/DsURl099Cog?a  via @YouTube |author=DanTDM |date=25 October 2016 |access-date=14 February 2017}}</ref> In 2017, he embarked on a tour through the United States and Australia.<ref>Grixti, Shannon (19 July 2017) [https://press-start.com.au/news/2017/07/19/youtuber-dantdm-touring-australia \"YOUTUBER DANTDM IS TOURING AUSTRALIA AGAIN\"] Press Start AU.</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.iq-mag.net/2017/02/live-nation-youtuber-dantdm-us-tour/#.WN7xvRiUU_U |title=Live Nation takes YouTuber DanTDM on US tour - IQ Magazine: Live Music Business News |last=IQ |date=15 February 2017 |website=iq-mag.net |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170818202921/https://www.iq-mag.net/2017/02/live-nation-youtuber-dantdm-us-tour/#.WN7xvRiUU_U |archive-date=18 August 2017 |access-date=1 April 2017 }}</ref>\n\nHis online video channel had focused primarily on the popular game ''[[Minecraft]]'', as of January 2020, he has allocated part of his channel to playing random video games, community Discord challenges and reaction videos. Middleton also maintains a [[Minecraft#Survival mode|Minecraft Hardcore]] series which is a substantial part of his channel.{{cn|date=March 2020}} He streams it live on Twitch and posts an edited version on his YouTube Channel.\n\nIn 2017, he starred in a web series called ''DanTDM Creates a Big Scene'' starring himself and featuring other social media entertainers and actors.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Milligan |first=Mercedes |url=http://www.animationmagazine.net/top-stories/youtube-red-slates-first-original-kids-shows/ |title=YouTube Red Slates First Original Kids Shows |date=16 February 2017 |work=Animation Magazine |access-date=15 June 2017 |language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://decider.com/2017/06/07/youtube-is-run-by-childrens-cartoons/ |title=YouTube Is Secretly Run By Insane CGI Kids Videos |date=7 June 2017 |website=Decider {{!}} Where To Stream Movies & Shows on Netflix, Hulu, Amazon Instant, HBO Go |access-date=15 June 2017}}</ref> The series premiered on 7 April 2017 exclusively for [[YouTube Red]], YouTube's subscription service,<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://geekdad.com/2017/04/dantdms-big-scene/ |title=DanTDM's 'Big Scene' Can Tide Diehard Fans Over - GeekDad |date=7 April 2017 |work=GeekDad |access-date=15 June 2017 |language=en-US}}</ref> The show \"follows DanTDM and his group of animated friends as they battle to keep their live show on the road\".<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://teneightymagazine.com/2017/12/28/11-youtubers-who-smashed-it-in-2017/ |title=11 YouTubers Who Smashed It In 2017 \u2013 TenEighty \u2014 YouTube News, Features, and Interviews |website=teneightymagazine.com |access-date=10 January 2018}}</ref> and ran for six episodes.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ZUE78MeQyzA |title=Draw My Show - DanTDM Creates a Big Scene (Ep 6) |last=DanTDM |date=5 May 2017 |via=YouTube}}</ref><ref>{{Citation |last=DanTDM |title=Save The Show - DanTDM Creates a Big Scene (Ep 1) |date=7 April 2017 |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=zKk_FIfOIyY&list=PLUR-PCZCUv7S2vTfGmue3uJ-DvVcZal26 |access-date=15 June 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nIn June 2013, when his channel exceeded 100,000 subscribers, he posted a video revealing his face for the first time ever.<ref name=\"100k subscribers\" /> Middleton married his girlfriend Jemma on 17 March 2013.<ref name=\"big issue\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.bigissue.com/features/interviews/3899/diamond-minecraft-interview-i-have-more-youtube-subscribers-than-the-bbc |title=Diamond Minecraft interview: \"I have more YouTube subscribers than the BBC\" |last=Lobb |first=Adrian |date=22 May 2014 |website=[[The Big Issue]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304024508/http://www.bigissue.com/features/interviews/3899/diamond-minecraft-interview-i-have-more-youtube-subscribers-than-the-bbc |archive-date=4 March 2016 |access-date=3 March 2016 }}</ref> The two have a son, Asher, born on 5 January 2020.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.instagram.com/p/B7G0rFUBEKa/ |title=Asher Middleton was born on the 5th January 2020. We couldn't be happier. We have made the decision not to show his face anywhere online so please respect our wishes. Thank you, I'll be back soon :) \ud83d\udc99 xx |website=Instagram |access-date=9 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\"\n|+ Film roles\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" | Year\n! scope=\"col\" | Title\n! scope=\"col\" | Role\n! scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 2018\n| ''[[Ralph Breaks the Internet]]''\n| eBoy\n| Voice role; UK version<ref>{{Cite AV media |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=xc34Lk7aHH4 |title=I'm in a DISNEY MOVIE! |date=27 November 2018 |last=Middleton |first=Daniel |access-date=23 November 2019 |website=[[YouTube]]}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2019\n| ''DanTDM Presents The Contest''{{citation needed|date=January 2020}}\n| Himself\n| Main voice of the flim.\n|}\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\"\n|+ Web roles\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" | Year\n! scope=\"col\" | Title\n! scope=\"col\" | Role\n! scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 2016\n| ''[[Skylanders Academy]]''\n| Cy\n| Voice role; recurring\n|-\n| 2017\n| ''DanTDM Creates A Big Scene''\n| Himself\n| [[YouTube Originals|YouTube Original series]]; 6 episodes\n|-\n| 2019\n| ''DanTDM Presents The Contest''{{Citation needed|date=January 2020}}\n| Himself\n| From the 2nd tour.\n|}\n\n==Awards and nominations==\n* [[Guinness World Record]] for \"Most goals scored in a game of ''[[Rocket League]]'' for a team of 2\".<ref name=\"MyUser_Guinnessworldrecords.com_October_17_2015c\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.guinnessworldrecords.com/news/2015/9/minecraft-and-rocket-league-records-smashed-at-legends-of-gaming-event-in-london-395623 |title=Minecraft and Rocket League records smashed at Legends of Gaming event in London |last=Doultrey |first=Stephen |date=9 September 2015 |website=[[Guinness World Records]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151016235325/http://www.guinnessworldrecords.com/news/2015/9/minecraft-and-rocket-league-records-smashed-at-legends-of-gaming-event-in-london-395623 |archive-date=16 October 2015 |access-date=17 October 2015 }}</ref> and \"Most goals scored in a game of Rocket League (team of three).\"<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.guinnessworldrecords.com/news/2015/12/dan-tdm-and-team-of-youtubers-smash-rocket-league-record-at-insomnia-gaming-festi-410064 |title=YouTube stars including Dan TDM smash Rocket League record at Insomnia gaming festival |date=14 December 2015 |website=guinnessworldrecords.com |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161012222717/http://www.guinnessworldrecords.com/news/2015/12/dan-tdm-and-team-of-youtubers-smash-rocket-league-record-at-insomnia-gaming-festi-410064 |archive-date=12 October 2016 |access-date=4 October 2016 }}</ref>\n* [[Guinness World Record]] for \"Most views for a dedicated [[Minecraft]] video channel\".<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.guinnessworldrecords.com/news/2016/10/youtuber-dan-tdm-enters-guinness-world-records-gamers-edition-for-minecraft-chan-448498 |title=Youtuber Dan TDM enters Guinness World Records Gamer's Edition for Minecraft channel |date=27 October 2016 |work=guinnessworldrecords.com |access-date=1 November 2016 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161030034552/http://www.guinnessworldrecords.com/news/2016/10/youtuber-dan-tdm-enters-guinness-world-records-gamers-edition-for-minecraft-chan-448498 |archive-date=30 October 2016 }}</ref>\n* [[Kids' Choice Awards|Nickelodeon Kids' Choice Awards]] in the category UK Favourite Tipster: [[2015 Kids' Choice Awards|2015]]<ref name=\"Nominees2015\">{{Cite web |url=http://kca.nick.co.uk/vote?category=UK-Favourite-Tipster |title=2015 Nickelodeon Kids' Choice Awards |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150502044913/http://kca.nick.co.uk/vote?category=UK-Favourite-Tipster |archive-date=2 May 2015 |access-date=11 February 2016 }}</ref> and [[2016 Kids' Choice Awards|2016]]<ref name=\"Nominees2016\">{{Cite web |url=http://kca.nick.co.uk/vote#cat=UK-Favourite-Tipster |title=2016 Nickelodeon Kids' Choice Awards \u2013 UK Favourite Tipster |website=2016 Nickelodeon Kids' Choice Awards |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130327235626/http://kca.nick.co.uk/vote#cat=UK-Favourite-Tipster |archive-date=27 March 2013 |access-date=19 March 2016 }}</ref>\n* [[Nickelodeon Kids' Choice Awards]] in the category UK Favourite Gamer 2020\n\n==Publications==\n* {{Cite book |author=DanTDM |date=6 October 2016 |title=[[Trayaurus and the Enchanted Crystal]] |publisher=[[HarperCollins]] |isbn=978-1409168393}}\n* {{Cite book |author=DanTDM |date=17 November 2016 |title=Official DanTDM 2017 Diary and Activity Book: Lots of Things to Make and Do |publisher=[[Orion Publishing Group|Trapeze]] |isbn=978-1409171188}}\n\n==Notes==\n{{notelist}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCm-X6o81nRsXQTmqpyArkBQ}}\n* {{IMDb name|nm7637737}}\n<!-- * {{Official website|http://www.thediamondminecart.com}} -->\n\n[[Category:1991 births]]\n[[Category:21st-century British male writers]]\n[[Category:21st-century English novelists]]\n[[Category:English male voice actors]]\n[[Category:English male web series actors]]\n[[Category:English male writers]]\n[[Category:English YouTubers]]\n[[Category:Let's Players]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Male YouTubers]]\n[[Category:People from Aldershot]]\n[[Category:Video game commentators]]\n[[Category:YouTube channels launched in 2012]]\n[[Category:YouTube Diamond Play Button recipients]]\n[[Category:YouTube Gold Play Button recipients]]\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nHELLO MY DUDES STAY SIX FEET APART PLEASE AND SUB TO FLAMINGO ON YOUtube\n", "text_old": "{{short description|British professional gamer and YouTuber}}\n{{Use British English|date=November 2016}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{Infobox YouTube personality\n| name            = DanTDM\n| image           = DanTDM2019.jpg\n| caption         = Middleton in 2019\n| birth_name      = Daniel Robert Middleton\n| birth_date      = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1991|11|8}}\n| birth_place     = [[Aldershot]], England\n| nationality     = British\n| residence       = [[Wellingborough]], England\n| occupation      = {{flatlist|\n* [[YouTuber]]\n* [[Let's Play|video game commentator]]\n}}\n| spouse          = {{marriage|Jemma Middleton|17 March 2013}}\n<!-- please do not add 'children' here, it is not a parameter in this template (see [[Template:Infobox YouTube personality]]) -->\n| pseudonym       = TheDiamondMinecart\n\n| channels        = {{flatlist|\n* [https://www.youtube.com/user/TheDiamondMinecart DanTDM]\n* [https://www.youtube.com/user/MoreTDM  MoreTDM]\n* [https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCa94pyq0HNK8qAFUBJiVAeA DanTDM Live]\n}}\n| years_active    = 2012\u2013present<!-- year of primary channel's creation until its discontinuation or present day -->\n| genre           = [[Video game culture|Gaming]] (focus on [[Minecraft]] and [[Fortnite]])\n| subscribers     = 22.6 million\n| views           = 16.5 billion <!-- round down to nearest .1 billion -->\n| stats_update    = 4 April 2020\n| silver_button   = yes\n| silver_year     = 2013<ref name=\"100k subscribers\">{{Cite AV media |url=//www.youtube.com/watch?v=bWOdn2C1PDc |title=TDM Vlogs \u2013 100,000 Subscribers, IRL & Events! |date=25 June 2013 |access-date=21 August 2016}}</ref>\n| gold_button     = yes\n| gold_year       = 2013<ref>{{Cite AV media |url=//www.youtube.com/watch?v=zk2_xuP4TNE |title=YouTube's Golden Award! \u2013 TheDiamondMinecart |date=17 September 2014 |last=The Diamond Minecart // DanTDM |access-date=11 February 2016 |via=YouTube}}</ref>\n| diamond_button  = yes\n| diamond_year    = 2016<ref>{{Cite web |url=//www.youtube.com/watch?v=IyJQInF9TiE |title=10 Million Subscribers!!!! |last=TheDiamondMinecart: DanTDM |date=28 March 2016 |via=YouTube |access-date=8 June 2016}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=//www.youtube.com/watch?v=30VbbiWSmHA |title=Our Diamond Play Button!!!! |last=TheDiamondMinecart: DanTDM |date=30 July 2016 |via=YouTube |access-date=30 July 2016}}</ref>\n}}\n'''Daniel Robert Middleton'''<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://beta.companieshouse.gov.uk/officers/7QepmF7pYH55RvCFGf2Utfw36GU/appointments |title=Daniel Robert MIDDLETON - Personal Appointments (free information from Companies House) |website=beta.companieshouse.gov.uk |access-date=10 January 2018}}</ref> (born 8 November 1991), known online as '''DanTDM''' (formerly '''The Diamond Minecart'''), is a British [[YouTuber|YouTube personality]] and professional gamer. His online video channels have covered many video games, mainly the popular games ''[[Minecraft]]'', ''[[Roblox]]'', and ''[[Pok\u00e9mon]]''.\n\nHis channel has been listed among the top YouTube channels in the [[United Kingdom]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://socialblade.com/youtube/top/country/gb/mostsubscribed |title=Top 100 YouTubers in United Kingdom Filtered by Subscribers |website=socialblade.com |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160330110614/http://socialblade.com/youtube/top/country/gb/mostsubscribed |archive-date=30 March 2016 |access-date=28 March 2016 }}</ref> In July 2015, he was listed as one of the most popular YouTubers in the world by viewership.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Dredge |first=Stuart |url=https://www.theguardian.com/technology/2015/aug/31/the-diamond-minecart-pewdiepie-youtube-minecraft |title=The Diamond Minecart becomes most popular YouTube channel |date=1 September 2015 |work=The Guardian |access-date=11 February 2016}}</ref> He has won several [[Kids' Choice Awards]] and set [[Guinness World Records]] for his gaming and presenting. In 2017, Middleton topped the [[Forbes]] list of Highest-Paid YouTube Stars, earning $16.5 million (about {{GBP|12.2 million}}) in one year.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.forbes.com/pictures/5a275d6931358e286471a7e8/1-daniel-middleton-dantdm/#28a09833343e |title=The World's Highest-Paid YouTube Stars 2017 |website=Forbes |publisher=Forbes |access-date=7 December 2017}}</ref> {{As of|2020|2|df=}}, Middleton has over 16 billion views, around 22.5 million subscribers and has posted more than 3,400 videos.\n\n==Early life==\nDaniel Middleton was born on 8 November 1991 in [[Aldershot]], England as the elder son of two siblings.<ref name=\"DrawMyLife\">{{Cite web |url=//www.youtube.com/watch?v=N2D9Y6lSFkw |title=Draw My Life - TheDiamondMinecart &#124; 1,000,000 Subscriber Special |last=DanTDM |date=10 December 2013 |publisher=YouTube |access-date=7 February 2015}}</ref> His parents divorced when he was little.<ref name=\"DrawMyLife\" /> He attended the [[University of Nottingham]], and started a YouTube channel in 2009 dedicated to [[Counter-Strike Global Offensive]] while at university, in which he called himself \"PokemanDanlvl45\".<ref>{{Cite web |url=//www.youtube.com/user/PokemanDanLv45 |title=PokemanDanLv45 |website=YouTube |access-date=20 March 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\nIn 2012, Middleton created ''The Diamond Minecart'', a gaming channel.<ref name=\"bbc 20140411\">{{Cite news |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-england-northamptonshire-26990297 |title=Dan Middleton's Minecraft videos a global hit |date=11 April 2014 |access-date=3 March 2016 |publisher=BBC News}}</ref> He changed his channel's name into ''TheDiamondMinecart // DanTDM'', and then, in 12 December 2016, to ''DanTDM''.<ref>{{Cite web |url=//www.youtube.com/watch?v=_mCiZxmZ7dQ |title=I'M CHANGING MY NAME... |last=DanTDM |date=12 December 2016 |via=YouTube |access-date=1 April 2017}}</ref>{{efn|Although DanTDM's channel name has changed, the channel still lists itself as TheDiamondMinecart within its URL.}} He currently produces videos out of his home studio in [[Wellingborough]].<ref name=\"bbc 20140411\" />\n\nHe released a graphic novel called ''[[Trayaurus and the Enchanted Crystal]]'' on 6 October 2016.<ref name=\"glou 20161012\" /><ref>{{Cite news |last=Cowdrey |first=Katherine |url=http://www.thebookseller.com/news/trapeze-publish-graphic-novel-youtubes-dan-diamond-minecart-330271 |title=YouTube's Dan the Diamond Minecart inks book deal - The Bookseller |work=The Bookseller |access-date=13 August 2016 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160826212251/http://www.thebookseller.com/news/trapeze-publish-graphic-novel-youtubes-dan-diamond-minecart-330271 |archive-date=26 August 2016 }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.publishersweekly.com/pw/by-topic/new-titles/on-sale-calendar/article/71090-the-on-sale-calendar-october-2016-children-s-books.html |title=The On-Sale Calendar October 2016 Children's Books |last=Staff |date=3 August 2016 |website=[[Publishers Weekly]] |access-date=13 August 2016}}</ref> The novel remained at the number one spot on [[The New York Times Best Seller list|''The New York Times'' Best Seller list]] for hardcover graphic books for eleven weeks.<ref>Listings on ''The New York Times'' Best Seller list per week: [https://www.nytimes.com/books/best-sellers/2016/11/13/hardcover-graphic-books/ Week 1], [https://www.nytimes.com/books/best-sellers/2016/11/20/hardcover-graphic-books/ Week 2], [https://www.nytimes.com/books/best-sellers/2016/11/27/hardcover-graphic-books/ Week 3], [https://www.nytimes.com/books/best-sellers/2016/12/04/hardcover-graphic-books/ Week 4], [https://www.nytimes.com/books/best-sellers/2016/12/11/hardcover-graphic-books/ Week 5], [https://www.nytimes.com/books/best-sellers/2016/12/18/hardcover-graphic-books/ Week 6], [https://www.nytimes.com/books/best-sellers/2016/12/25/hardcover-graphic-books/ Week 7], [https://www.nytimes.com/books/best-sellers/2017/01/01/hardcover-graphic-books/ Week 8], [https://www.nytimes.com/books/best-sellers/2017/01/08/hardcover-graphic-books/ Week 9], [https://www.nytimes.com/books/best-sellers/2017/01/15/hardcover-graphic-books/ Week 10], [https://www.nytimes.com/books/best-sellers/2017/01/22/hardcover-graphic-books/ Week 11], [https://www.nytimes.com/books/best-sellers/2017/01/29/hardcover-graphic-books/ Week 12, when it fell to the second spot].</ref> He was a featured guest at the [[Cheltenham Literature Festival]] and went on a book tour that included parts of the UK and a visit to [[New York City]].<ref name=\"glou 20161012\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.gloucestershirelive.co.uk/bet-you-haven-8217-t-heard-of-the-biggest-star-at-the-cheltenham-literature-festival-2016/story-29780498-detail/story.html |title=Bet you've not heard of the biggest star at literature festival? |last=Merrell |first=Andrew |date=5 October 2016 |website=Gloucestershire Live |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161012152035/http://www.gloucestershirelive.co.uk/bet-you-haven-8217-t-heard-of-the-biggest-star-at-the-cheltenham-literature-festival-2016/story-29780498-detail/story.html |archive-date=12 October 2016 |access-date=12 October 2016 }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.gloucestershirelive.co.uk/hundreds-rush-waterstones-tent-at-cheltenham-literature-festival-to-get-a-glimpse-of-dantdm/story-29799439-detail/story.html |title=Hundreds rush Cheltenham Literature Festival tent to reach DanTDM |last=Merrell |first=Andrew |date=11 October 2016 |website=Gloucestershire Live |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161012235110/http://www.gloucestershirelive.co.uk/hundreds-rush-waterstones-tent-at-cheltenham-literature-festival-to-get-a-glimpse-of-dantdm/story-29799439-detail/story.html |archive-date=12 October 2016 |access-date=12 October 2016 }}</ref><ref name=\"geek dad\">{{Cite web |url=https://geekdad.com/2016/11/dantdms-new-graphic-novel/ |title=Take 'Minecraft' to the Next (Reading) Level With DanTDM's New Graphic Novel - GeekDad |last=Knox |first=Kelly |date=25 November 2016 |website=geekdad.com |access-date=21 September 2017}}</ref><ref>{{Cite tweet |number=790996720717008896 |user=dantdm |title=MY BOOK IN THE U.S. & MINI U.S. BOOK TOUR!!!: http://youtu.be/DsURl099Cog?a  via @YouTube |author=DanTDM |date=25 October 2016 |access-date=14 February 2017}}</ref> In 2017, he embarked on a tour through the United States and Australia.<ref>Grixti, Shannon (19 July 2017) [https://press-start.com.au/news/2017/07/19/youtuber-dantdm-touring-australia \"YOUTUBER DANTDM IS TOURING AUSTRALIA AGAIN\"] Press Start AU.</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.iq-mag.net/2017/02/live-nation-youtuber-dantdm-us-tour/#.WN7xvRiUU_U |title=Live Nation takes YouTuber DanTDM on US tour - IQ Magazine: Live Music Business News |last=IQ |date=15 February 2017 |website=iq-mag.net |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170818202921/https://www.iq-mag.net/2017/02/live-nation-youtuber-dantdm-us-tour/#.WN7xvRiUU_U |archive-date=18 August 2017 |access-date=1 April 2017 }}</ref>\n\nHis online video channel had focused primarily on the popular game ''[[Minecraft]]'', as of January 2020, he has allocated part of his channel to playing random video games, community Discord challenges and reaction videos. Middleton also maintains a [[Minecraft#Survival mode|Minecraft Hardcore]] series which is a substantial part of his channel.{{cn|date=March 2020}} He streams it live on Twitch and posts an edited version on his YouTube Channel.\n\nIn 2017, he starred in a web series called ''DanTDM Creates a Big Scene'' starring himself and featuring other social media entertainers and actors.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Milligan |first=Mercedes |url=http://www.animationmagazine.net/top-stories/youtube-red-slates-first-original-kids-shows/ |title=YouTube Red Slates First Original Kids Shows |date=16 February 2017 |work=Animation Magazine |access-date=15 June 2017 |language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://decider.com/2017/06/07/youtube-is-run-by-childrens-cartoons/ |title=YouTube Is Secretly Run By Insane CGI Kids Videos |date=7 June 2017 |website=Decider {{!}} Where To Stream Movies & Shows on Netflix, Hulu, Amazon Instant, HBO Go |access-date=15 June 2017}}</ref> The series premiered on 7 April 2017 exclusively for [[YouTube Red]], YouTube's subscription service,<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://geekdad.com/2017/04/dantdms-big-scene/ |title=DanTDM's 'Big Scene' Can Tide Diehard Fans Over - GeekDad |date=7 April 2017 |work=GeekDad |access-date=15 June 2017 |language=en-US}}</ref> The show \"follows DanTDM and his group of animated friends as they battle to keep their live show on the road\".<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://teneightymagazine.com/2017/12/28/11-youtubers-who-smashed-it-in-2017/ |title=11 YouTubers Who Smashed It In 2017 \u2013 TenEighty \u2014 YouTube News, Features, and Interviews |website=teneightymagazine.com |access-date=10 January 2018}}</ref> and ran for six episodes.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ZUE78MeQyzA |title=Draw My Show - DanTDM Creates a Big Scene (Ep 6) |last=DanTDM |date=5 May 2017 |via=YouTube}}</ref><ref>{{Citation |last=DanTDM |title=Save The Show - DanTDM Creates a Big Scene (Ep 1) |date=7 April 2017 |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=zKk_FIfOIyY&list=PLUR-PCZCUv7S2vTfGmue3uJ-DvVcZal26 |access-date=15 June 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nIn June 2013, when his channel exceeded 100,000 subscribers, he posted a video revealing his face for the first time ever.<ref name=\"100k subscribers\" /> Middleton married his girlfriend Jemma on 17 March 2013.<ref name=\"big issue\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.bigissue.com/features/interviews/3899/diamond-minecraft-interview-i-have-more-youtube-subscribers-than-the-bbc |title=Diamond Minecraft interview: \"I have more YouTube subscribers than the BBC\" |last=Lobb |first=Adrian |date=22 May 2014 |website=[[The Big Issue]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304024508/http://www.bigissue.com/features/interviews/3899/diamond-minecraft-interview-i-have-more-youtube-subscribers-than-the-bbc |archive-date=4 March 2016 |access-date=3 March 2016 }}</ref> The two have a son, Asher, born on 5 January 2020.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.instagram.com/p/B7G0rFUBEKa/ |title=Asher Middleton was born on the 5th January 2020. We couldn't be happier. We have made the decision not to show his face anywhere online so please respect our wishes. Thank you, I'll be back soon :) \ud83d\udc99 xx |website=Instagram |access-date=9 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\"\n|+ Film roles\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" | Year\n! scope=\"col\" | Title\n! scope=\"col\" | Role\n! scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 2018\n| ''[[Ralph Breaks the Internet]]''\n| eBoy\n| Voice role; UK version<ref>{{Cite AV media |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=xc34Lk7aHH4 |title=I'm in a DISNEY MOVIE! |date=27 November 2018 |last=Middleton |first=Daniel |access-date=23 November 2019 |website=[[YouTube]]}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2019\n| ''DanTDM Presents The Contest''{{citation needed|date=January 2020}}\n| Himself\n| Main voice of the flim.\n|}\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\"\n|+ Web roles\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" | Year\n! scope=\"col\" | Title\n! scope=\"col\" | Role\n! scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 2016\n| ''[[Skylanders Academy]]''\n| Cy\n| Voice role; recurring\n|-\n| 2017\n| ''DanTDM Creates A Big Scene''\n| Himself\n| [[YouTube Originals|YouTube Original series]]; 6 episodes\n|-\n| 2019\n| ''DanTDM Presents The Contest''{{Citation needed|date=January 2020}}\n| Himself\n| From the 2nd tour.\n|}\n\n==Awards and nominations==\n* [[Guinness World Record]] for \"Most goals scored in a game of ''[[Rocket League]]'' for a team of 2\".<ref name=\"MyUser_Guinnessworldrecords.com_October_17_2015c\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.guinnessworldrecords.com/news/2015/9/minecraft-and-rocket-league-records-smashed-at-legends-of-gaming-event-in-london-395623 |title=Minecraft and Rocket League records smashed at Legends of Gaming event in London |last=Doultrey |first=Stephen |date=9 September 2015 |website=[[Guinness World Records]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151016235325/http://www.guinnessworldrecords.com/news/2015/9/minecraft-and-rocket-league-records-smashed-at-legends-of-gaming-event-in-london-395623 |archive-date=16 October 2015 |access-date=17 October 2015 }}</ref> and \"Most goals scored in a game of Rocket League (team of three).\"<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.guinnessworldrecords.com/news/2015/12/dan-tdm-and-team-of-youtubers-smash-rocket-league-record-at-insomnia-gaming-festi-410064 |title=YouTube stars including Dan TDM smash Rocket League record at Insomnia gaming festival |date=14 December 2015 |website=guinnessworldrecords.com |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161012222717/http://www.guinnessworldrecords.com/news/2015/12/dan-tdm-and-team-of-youtubers-smash-rocket-league-record-at-insomnia-gaming-festi-410064 |archive-date=12 October 2016 |access-date=4 October 2016 }}</ref>\n* [[Guinness World Record]] for \"Most views for a dedicated [[Minecraft]] video channel\".<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.guinnessworldrecords.com/news/2016/10/youtuber-dan-tdm-enters-guinness-world-records-gamers-edition-for-minecraft-chan-448498 |title=Youtuber Dan TDM enters Guinness World Records Gamer's Edition for Minecraft channel |date=27 October 2016 |work=guinnessworldrecords.com |access-date=1 November 2016 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161030034552/http://www.guinnessworldrecords.com/news/2016/10/youtuber-dan-tdm-enters-guinness-world-records-gamers-edition-for-minecraft-chan-448498 |archive-date=30 October 2016 }}</ref>\n* [[Kids' Choice Awards|Nickelodeon Kids' Choice Awards]] in the category UK Favourite Tipster: [[2015 Kids' Choice Awards|2015]]<ref name=\"Nominees2015\">{{Cite web |url=http://kca.nick.co.uk/vote?category=UK-Favourite-Tipster |title=2015 Nickelodeon Kids' Choice Awards |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150502044913/http://kca.nick.co.uk/vote?category=UK-Favourite-Tipster |archive-date=2 May 2015 |access-date=11 February 2016 }}</ref> and [[2016 Kids' Choice Awards|2016]]<ref name=\"Nominees2016\">{{Cite web |url=http://kca.nick.co.uk/vote#cat=UK-Favourite-Tipster |title=2016 Nickelodeon Kids' Choice Awards \u2013 UK Favourite Tipster |website=2016 Nickelodeon Kids' Choice Awards |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130327235626/http://kca.nick.co.uk/vote#cat=UK-Favourite-Tipster |archive-date=27 March 2013 |access-date=19 March 2016 }}</ref>\n* [[Nickelodeon Kids' Choice Awards]] in the category UK Favourite Gamer 2020\n\n==Publications==\n* {{Cite book |author=DanTDM |date=6 October 2016 |title=[[Trayaurus and the Enchanted Crystal]] |publisher=[[HarperCollins]] |isbn=978-1409168393}}\n* {{Cite book |author=DanTDM |date=17 November 2016 |title=Official DanTDM 2017 Diary and Activity Book: Lots of Things to Make and Do |publisher=[[Orion Publishing Group|Trapeze]] |isbn=978-1409171188}}\n\n==Notes==\n{{notelist}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{YouTube|u=TheDiamondMinecart}}\n* {{IMDb name|nm7637737}}\n<!-- * {{Official website|http://www.thediamondminecart.com}} -->\n\n[[Category:1991 births]]\n[[Category:21st-century British male writers]]\n[[Category:21st-century English novelists]]\n[[Category:English male voice actors]]\n[[Category:English male web series actors]]\n[[Category:English male writers]]\n[[Category:English YouTubers]]\n[[Category:Let's Players]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Male YouTubers]]\n[[Category: